1. *Plakala* sam kada sam čula tužnu vijest. (I cried when I heard the sad news.)
2. Ona je sinoć *plakala* cijelu noć. (She cried all night last night.)
3. Kada je vidjela svoju kuću u plamenu, odmah je *plakala*. (When she saw her house in flames, she immediately burst into tears.)
4. Njena majka je uvijek bila tu kada je ona *plakala*. (Her mother was always there when she cried.)
5. Nikada ne bih pomislio da će ona *plakati* zbog takvih sitnica. (I never thought she would cry over such small things.)
6. Kada sam je pitao zašto *plače*, nije željela da mi kaže. (When I asked her why she was crying, she didn't want to tell me.)
7. Nije htjela da me vidi kako *plačem*, pa je otišla iz sobe. (She didn't want to see me cry, so she left the room.)
8. Kada su joj rekli da ne može da ima djecu, ona je *plakala* danima. (When they told her she couldn't have children, she cried for days.)